uk.ac.ucl.rits.inform

Class HL7Processor

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ucl.rits.inform.HL7Processor

  • public class HL7Processor
extends Object
    HL7Processor was written for the autumn 2018 demo. It extracts data from the IDS (DUMMY_IDS) and writes relevant info to the UDS (INFORM_SCRATCH)

    To compile and run: 

     mvn compile
 mvn test
 mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="uk.ac.ucl.rits.inform.HL7Processor"
 mvn javadoc:javadoc
    A typical location value is T11S^B11S^T11S-32

    NB this demo code is intended to be single threaded. Later might want to use things like ConcurrentHashMap.

    From PostgresApp documentation https://postgresapp.com/documentation/cli-tools.html to install the App: 

     sudo mkdir -p /etc/paths.d 
 sudo echo /Applications/Postgres.app/Contents/Versions/latest/bin | sudo tee /etc/paths.d/postgresapp

      • check_json_value

        public static Object[] check_json_value(org.json.simple.JSONObject jo,
                                        String variable,
                                        String keystring)
        Robustly check JSON object for a required value. When debugging is on, key may be missing from config file/JSONObject.
        Parameters:
        jo - The JSON object being queried.
        variable - Name of a global String object, e.g. idsusername;
        keystring - Name of the key in the JSON object map/config file, e.g. IDSUSERNAMESTR
        Returns:
        double of Objects. First element is true if key and value found, false otherwise. If true, second element is new variable value.

      • convert_timestamp

        public static String convert_timestamp(String hl7)
        Convert HL7 format timestamp into a Postgres one.

        NB some HL7 timestamps won't have the decimal part. And some will only be accurate to the day (so no hhmmss information)

        Unfortunately, Ashish says the precision is the same as what he sent me in the test messages, which is to the nearest second. However we don't worry about that in this method.

        Parameters:
        hl7 - An HL7 format timestamp e.g. "20181003141807.7618"
        Returns:
        Postgres-format timestamp e.g. "2018-10-03 14:18:07.7618"
